Package: TextAnalysisR
Title: A Text Mining Workflow Tool
Version: 0.0.3
Date: 2025-12-27
Authors@R:
    person("Mikyung", "Shin", , "shin.mikyung@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7907-9193", affiliation = "Illinois State University"))
Description: Comprehensive toolkit for text mining and natural language processing with
    an interactive 'Shiny' interface. Import documents from multiple formats (PDF, DOCX,
    XLSX, CSV, TXT) using 'Marker' for PDF extraction, preprocess with 'quanteda', and
    perform linguistic analysis via 'spaCy', topic modeling ('stm', 'BERTopic'),
    semantic analysis, sentiment analysis, and network visualization with 'plotly'.
    Features topic-grounded content generation and AI-suggested labeling via local
    ('Ollama', 'spaCy', transformers) and web-based ('OpenAI', 'Gemini') APIs,
    WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility, multi-language support, and enterprise security for
    production deployment.
